{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> αὔριον</b>, <br /> <i>adverb</i> <b>to-morrow,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.357, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 1.272, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; αὔ. τηνικάδε <b>tomorrow</b> at this time, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 76b\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐς or εἰς αὔ. <b>on the morrow,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 8.538\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] (or <b>till morning,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 11.351), 4th c.BC: Nicochares Comicus 15, 4th c.BC: Anaxandrides Comicus 4.4\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>for the morrow,</b> καλέσαι ἐπὶ δεῖπνον εἰς αὔ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 22.17, etc. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>presently, shortly,</b> φάγωμεν καὶ πίωμεν, αὔ. γὰρ ἀποθνῄσκομεν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.1Cor.15.32\">NT</a>]; opposed to σήμερον, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Matt.6.30. \">NT</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>substantive</i>, αὔ. ἣν ἀρετὴν διαείσεται <b>the morrow</b> will distinguish.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 8.535. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> ἡ αὔ. (i.e. ἡμέρα) <b>the morrow,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 945 (“OT” 1090 is corrupt); τὴν αὔ. μέλλουσαν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 784; ἡ αὔ. ἡμέρα 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Oeconomicus” 11.6, 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 26.6; also ἡ ἐς αὔ. ἡμέρα 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 567; τὸ ἐς αὔριον [prev. author] “fragment” 593.5; εἰς τὴν αὔ. 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 241.3, NT.Act.4.3\">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπὶ τὴν αὔ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 5; ὁ αὔ. χρόνος 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 1117\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἡ Αὔ. personified by [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Simonides Lyricus 210 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus; δαίμονα τὸν Αὔριον 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Epigrammata” 16\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. (Cf. Lithuanian <i>aušrà</i> 'dawn', Sanskrit <i>usrás</i> 'of the dawn'; see at {ἄγχαυρος},{ἕως}.)","strongNumber":"G0839","accentedUnicode":"αὔριον","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0109","matchingForm":"ἀήρ","stepTransliteration":"aēr","gloss":"air","_zh_tw_Gloss":"空中","_es_Gloss":"aire","_zh_Gloss":"空中"},{"strongNumber":"G1887","matchingForm":"ἐπαύριον","stepTransliteration":"epaurion","gloss":"the next day","_zh_tw_Gloss":"第二天","_es_Gloss":"el día siguiente ","_zh_Gloss":"第二天"},{"strongNumber":"G2250","matchingForm":"ἡμέρα","stepTransliteration":"hēmera","gloss":"day","_zh_tw_Gloss":"日子","_es_Gloss":"día","_zh_Gloss":"日子"}],"shortDef":"tomorrow, the next day","mediumDef":"tomorrow, the next day <br /><b>tomorrow,</b> <ref='Mat.6.30'>Mt. 6:30</ref>; <greek>ἡ αὔριον</greek>, <i>i.e.</i> <greek>ἡμέρα</greek>, <b>the next day,</b> <ref='Mat.6.34'>Mt. 6:34</ref>","stepGloss":"tomorrow","stepTransliteration":"aurion","count":15,"_es_Definition":"adv. mañana, el día siguiente ; en poco tiempo, pronto","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 隔天<br>2) 一會兒, 即將","_zh_Definition":"1) 隔天<br>2) 一会儿, 即将","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"mai; ngày mai","_zh_tw_Gloss":"明天","_es_Gloss":"mañana","_zh_Gloss":"明天"}]}